Session 8 (Hybrid VPN + IPSec + Tunnel concepts) is a classic CCEE trap-heavy area, especially mode differences, split tunneling risks, and RRAS-based VPNs.

Below are 30 CDAC-aligned MCQs (10 Basic + 10 Intermediate + 10 Advanced) covering Session 8 + Lab 13, exactly from PG-DITISS August 2025 perspective.

Network Defense & Countermeasures ‚Äì Session 8
BASIC MCQs (1‚Äì10)
1. A Hybrid VPN is best described as:
A. VPN using only public networks
B. Combination of Trusted VPN and Secure VPN
C. VPN without encryption
D. Mobile-only VPN

2. IPSec primarily operates at which OSI layer?
A. Application
B. Transport
C. Network
D. Data Link

3. IPSec ensures security mainly by using:
A. FTP and HTTP
B. AH and ESP protocols
C. SSL and TLS
D. GRE only

4. Tunnel mode in IPSec protects:
A. Payload only
B. Header only
C. Entire IP packet
D. Application data only

5. Transport mode in IPSec protects:
A. Entire IP packet
B. Payload only
C. IP header only
D. Routing table

6. Which VPN type is BEST suited for site-to-site connectivity?
A. Transport mode IPSec
B. Tunnel mode IPSec
C. PPTP
D. SSL VPN

7. Split tunneling means:
A. Blocking all traffic
B. Sending VPN traffic and internet traffic separately
C. Encrypting all traffic
D. Using two VPN servers

8. Full tunnel VPN ensures:
A. Only corporate traffic is encrypted
B. All traffic passes through VPN
C. Faster internet
D. No encryption

9. IPv6 VPN support in IPSec exists because:
A. IPv6 has no security
B. IPSec is mandatory in IPv6 standard
C. IPv6 cannot use SSL
D. IPv6 uses GRE

10. RRAS in Windows Server is used for:
A. IDS
B. Firewall
C. VPN and routing
D. Antivirus

INTERMEDIATE MCQs (11‚Äì20)
11. Which IPSec component provides confidentiality?
A. AH
B. ESP
C. IKE
D. ISAKMP

12. IPSec Authentication Header (AH) provides:
A. Encryption only
B. Integrity and authentication
C. Confidentiality
D. NAT traversal

13. IPSec ESP provides:
A. Authentication only
B. Integrity only
C. Confidentiality, integrity, authentication
D. Routing

14. Tunnel mode is preferred over transport mode mainly because:
A. It is faster
B. It hides internal IP addressing
C. It uses less CPU
D. It disables NAT

15. Split tunneling introduces which security risk?
A. Reduced bandwidth
B. Increased latency
C. Data leakage
D. Encryption overhead

16. PPTP is considered insecure mainly because it:
A. Uses AES
B. Has weak encryption and authentication
C. Is slow
D. Is complex

17. L2TP VPN is usually combined with IPSec because:
A. L2TP has encryption
B. IPSec adds security to L2TP
C. IPSec needs L2TP
D. L2TP improves speed

18. In Windows RRAS, which authentication method is most secure?
A. PAP
B. CHAP
C. MS-CHAPv2
D. EAP-TLS

19. IPv6 VPN configuration challenges arise mainly due to:
A. No encryption support
B. Addressing complexity
C. NAT usage
D. Lack of protocols

20. Which VPN setup is MOST suitable for remote employees?
A. Tunnel mode site-to-site
B. Transport mode IPSec
C. Remote access VPN
D. Hybrid VPN only

ADVANCED MCQs (21‚Äì30)
21. From security perspective, full tunnel VPN is preferred because it:
A. Saves bandwidth
B. Prevents split tunneling attacks
C. Disables firewall
D. Improves speed

22. IPSec NAT traversal (NAT-T) is required because:
A. AH breaks with NAT
B. ESP cannot work over UDP
C. NAT modifies IP headers
D. NAT blocks SSL

23. Hybrid VPN architecture is MOST useful when:
A. Only private networks exist
B. Mixing MPLS and internet-based VPNs
C. No encryption is needed
D. Only mobile devices connect

24. RRAS-based VPN security depends heavily on:
A. CPU speed
B. Proper authentication and policies
C. GUI design
D. Routing metrics

25. In IPSec tunnel mode, packet flow is best described as:
A. Original packet encrypted inside new IP packet
B. Only payload encrypted
C. Header sent in clear
D. No encapsulation

26. Which VPN misconfiguration MOST often leads to data leaks?
A. Weak encryption
B. Split tunneling enabled unnecessarily
C. Tunnel mode usage
D. IPv6 support

27. IPv6 IPSec integration improves security mainly by:
A. Making IPSec optional
B. Native protocol-level security support
C. Removing authentication
D. Replacing firewalls

28. L2TP/IPSec VPN provides better security than PPTP because it:
A. Uses GRE
B. Uses stronger encryption and authentication
C. Is faster
D. Uses less CPU

29. From CDAC exam perspective, which statement is MOST correct?
A. Split tunneling is always insecure
B. IPSec transport mode is obsolete
C. VPN modes depend on use case
D. PPTP is secure enough

30. Which statement BEST aligns with CDAC philosophy?
A. VPN guarantees complete security
B. Hybrid VPN reduces cost and risk
C. IPSec eliminates all threats
D. Full tunnel VPN is unnecessary

ANSWER KEY
Basic:
1-B, 2-C, 3-B, 4-C, 5-B, 6-B, 7-B, 8-B, 9-B, 10-C

Intermediate:
11-B, 12-B, 13-C, 14-B, 15-C, 16-B, 17-B, 18-D, 19-B, 20-C

Advanced:
21-B, 22-C, 23-B, 24-B, 25-A, 26-B, 27-B, 28-B, 29-C, 30-B

